>>529513268
The EU charter itself has articles similar to NATO's Article 5, but afaik lacks the explicit provision that your country cannot be instigator in the conflict. It obliges the entirety of the EU to come to the aid of one of their members.
As for NATO: one of the other treaty articles applying uniquely to its European members, which are also EU members and thus tied to aforementioned EU charter, is that they are allowed to coopt NATO assets for their own military purposes in the interests of the defense of the EU should NATO itself formally decide not to act.

In short, if you attack the EU it's an even faster track to NATO retaliation than attacking actual NATO. The sole holdback is the fact that the EU charter's required assistance is discretionatory, and it's up to the other member states to see how much they can reasonably contribute to a collective defensive or counter-offensive effort. They don't have to go 'all-in' all at once. But if you screw the pooch badly enough, they will.

(Humorously, if the US were to have actually attacked Greenland then Denmark could've coopted US military assets across the EU to come to Greenland's defense under the NATO banner. Yes. Really.)

Threadly reminder that you can feed shitbulls 0.5g per kg of body weight of xylitol and most will drop dead in a few days. Median weight 30kg shitbull, 15g of xylitol. "XL Bully" 90kg "shitbull mix", 45g of xylitol.

Xylitol is a sugar substitute that is safe for humans (and also kitties!) but lethal to dogs. It is widely available in granular form in health-food stores. (IOW, no, you don't need to feed the dog ten packs of chewing gum.) Just mix it into a doggie treat like sausage or cheese balls.

Xylitol has two separate modes of lethality in dogs: first, the chance of putting the dog into a hypoglycemic coma (within hours), second, liver failure (within days). The above doses are the LD50 (meaning half will die from it) to cause liver failure; the hypoglycemic coma dosage is only 20% of the above. There is no antidote, but it can be treated if caught early, and only about half of dogs will die from a LD50 dose (by definition). The two different modes make it very likely to kill a dog with this dose.

Avoid getting caught on video or making it obvious that you're the prime suspect by complaining constantly ahead of time.

Good way to rid your neighborhood of dangerous dogs.

Common counter-suggestions and why they aren't as good:
>just shoot it!
* police investigate gunshot wounds/deaths
* dangerous to bystanders in suburban or urban neighborhoods
* unless the dog is actually attacking you or someone else, this will get you criminally charged if caught

>antifreeze!
* takes literally 3X the dosage to reach LD50
* now has bitterants added to stop children and animals from drinking it
* weird options like boiling hotdogs in it makes your intent obvious

>rat poison or other poisons!
* obvious intent
* can be fatal to children or other animals you don't want to harm
* much more recognizable and hence treatable by a vet

Its funny you should ask that becasue I just did.
In HOI3 ( Hearts of Iron ) playing as Britain,
The trick is not to declare war until you have transports packed with troops sitting off the coast of Washington DC, Corpus Christi, and Panama.
Make sure each transport fleet is supported by a Carrier fleet.
Build lots of convoys so you can keep your guys supplied.
Have loads of spare CAGs ( Carrier Air Groups ) so you can replace worn out wings when the USN emerges from its ports and engages you.
The naval battles will be bloody affairs, the USN is strong and you will lose ships, ( I lost two carriers, and a host of escorts ) but you will have time to disembark your troops, and that is all that matters.
You can do this as early as 1938 by declaring war on Brazil. That annoys the Yanks so much you enter into a state of war with them automatically. Nice.
Once the flag goes up its easy. The US forces so early in the war are mostly unmobilized and lack infantry techs, they are a pushover for full strength up to date British divisions.
With the wide open spaces is easy enough to surround and destroy the few US divisions that can make a stand. You dont want those Blighters doing something silly like retreating to the mountains and making a last stand becasue it slows things down.
It still takes a while to annex the USA because all the Victory points are so spread out, you basically have to take most of them which means marching into the wops, places like Nevada, the Dakotas, and Colorado. Its a bit of a grind. Takes about 6 months, but once the intial US army is wiped its pretty much unopposed except for a few scattered doughboys.
So basically one force advances from Washington across the East coast, another forces marches north west from Texas, and the last forces snatches the West coast.
You can do shit like strategic bombing but by the time it takes effect the war is nearly over.
Anyway, hope this has been of some help! Good luck!
